<P>
SEASON'S FIRST SNOW IN TETON MOUNTAINS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The first snow of the season dusted the Teton Mountains of Wyoming and heavy 
rainfall drenched much of the nation. There was flooding in Oklahoma and 
Kansas. Some rural roads remained impassable in portions of Maryland, where an 
official reported holes up to 20 feet wide and 10 feet deep following weekend 
flooding. Showers and thunderstorms soaked the Florida peninsula, across New 
York state and portions of New England. But it was summer as usual with 
temperatures in the 90s in the middle and southern Atlantic coast states, the 
Gulf Coast, lower Mississippi Valley, the southern plains, the interior valleys 
of California, the desert Southwest and near the big bend of the Rio Grande in 
Texas. 
</P>
