<HEADLINE>
<P>
FIANCE SHOT TO DEATH, BUT FILIPINO BRIDE GOES AHEAD WITH HER WEDDING CEREMONY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
MANILA 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Evangeline Guico said her marriage vows Sunday, then sprinkled holy water over 
her fiance as he lay in a casket. 
</P>
<P>
Guico, 21, who is two months pregnant, was to have wed 21-year-old Marlon 
Manalac on Sept. 26 after a three-year courtship. But on Tuesday, Manalac was 
found shot to death by an unknown assailant in a Manila suburb. 
</P>
<P>
Manalac's father, police Maj. Alfonso Manalac, decided to go ahead with the 
unusual ceremony, which took place at the family residence. A minister of the 
Aglipayan Church, a Philippine denomination that broke with Roman Catholicism, 
agreed to officiate. Manalac's brother stood in for him at the ceremony. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Wire 
</P>
</TYPE>
<SUBJECT>
<P>
WEDDINGS; MURDERS -- PHILIPPINES; PHILIPPINES -- CULTURE 
</P>
</SUBJECT>
