<HEADLINE>
<P>
NIBBLES AND BITS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KDOC-TV Channel 56 has added two staff reporters to its "NewsWatch" broadcast, 
the only regularly scheduled television news program originating in Orange 
County, according to station spokesperson Tricia Krause. The general assignment 
reporters, Christopher Heinbaugh and Beth Bingham, bring the on-camera news 
team to 5, including reporter Jerilyn Donovan and anchors Michelle Merker and 
Pat Matthews. Heinbaugh, a Cal State Northridge graduation, was a news writer 
at KNX radio before joining "NewsWatch," which airs weeknights at 8:30 p.m. 
Bingham, a graduate of UC San Diego, worked for an NBC television affiliate in 
Macon, Ga., before returning to Southern California. She will also host the 
station's weekly public affairs program, "Southland Today." Krause said that, 
with the addition of the two reporters, "NewsWatch" averages four Orange County 
stories per night. 
</P>
