<TEXT>
<P>
Vestron Inc., which recently laid off about 140 employees after losing a 
$100-million line of credit, today reported a second quarter net loss of $65 
million. 
</P>
<P>
The film and video company blamed the loss on the writedown of motion picture 
assets resulting from the restructuring of Vestron's operations two months ago 
and a substantial decline in revenue for the period. 
</P>
