<HEADLINE>
<P>
ON THE SIDELINES; 
</P>
<P>
MCMAHON TO START AGAINST 49ERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
LA JOLLA 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Newly acquired quarterback Jim McMahon will start San Diego's exhibition game 
Wednesday night at San Francisco, Chargers Coach Dan Henning said. 
</P>
<P>
San Diego acquired the eight-year veteran last Friday from the Chicago Bears 
for a conditional 1990 draft choice. McMahon took the first four snaps of the 
second half against his former teammates on Saturday in a game the Chargers won 
24-7 at Chicago. 
</P>
<P>
While the rest of the Chargers relaxed before Sunday afternoon's practice, 
McMahon spent four hours with quarterback Coach Ted Tollner preparing for the 
San Francisco game. 
</P>
</TEXT>
